laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar dependent atelectasis; normal heart; multiple hypodensities in the spleen measuring up to 8 mm; kidneys take up and excrete contrast without hydronephrosis; normal small bowel; no free air or fluid; pronounced atherosclerotic calcifications; patent celiac axis and SMA; patent portal vein without thrombosis; florid sigmoidal diverticulosis; fat stranding in central to right-sided colon; developing phlegmon; locules of air suggesting microperforation; marked prostatic enlargement to 9.0 x 7.4 cm.
